Definition: a system of philosophical and theological doctrines composed of elements of Platonism and Aristotelianism and oriental mysticism
Example: its most distinctive doctrine holds that the first principle and source of reality transcends being and thought and is naturally unknowable; Neoplatonism was predominant in pagan Europe until the 6th century; Neoplatonism was a major influence on early Christian writers and on later medieval and Renaissance thought and on Islamic philosophy
Synonyms: philosophical_doctrine, theological_doctrine, a, system, of, philosophical, and, theological, doctrines, composed, elements, Platonism, Aristotelianism, oriental, mysticism, its, most, distinctive, doctrine, holds, that, the, first, principle, source, reality, transcends, being, thought, is, naturally, unknowable, was, predominant, in, pagan, Europe, until, th, century, major, influence, on, early, Christian, writers, later, medieval, Renaissance, Islamic, philosophy
Category: noun.cognition
